headline: The Dow Is Missing Out on the AMD Rally
summary: The blue-chip index, which weighs its members by stock price rather than market cap, fell sharply on a day when the Nasdaq and the S&P 500 were on track for record closing highs.  The Dow was down 266 points, or 0.6%.  Only 10 stocks in the index were rising, and some of its heaviest hitters—Sherwin-Williams, Home Depot, McDonald’s, and Salesforce—were big laggards.

headline: AstraZeneca Upgraded, Home Depot Downgraded: Updated Rankings on Top Blue-Chip Stocks
summary: During these busy times, it pays to stay on top of the latest profit opportunities. And today’s blog post should be a great place to start. After taking a close look at the latest data on institutional buying pressure and each company’s fundamental health, I decided to revise my Stock Grader recommendations for 149 big blue chips.
